title: Massive hurricane to strike western Mexico
text: National Hurricane Centre is still reporting maximum sustained winds of 200mph.What a beast! IndeedNormally it peaks and the tails off, but you can see from the below it is still up there. http://www.wunderground.com/hurricane/eastern-paci... Point to note that is max winds, gusts will be higher though. 250mph maybe. That's like an F4 to F5 tornado over a bigger area. It will lessen as it gets to interacting with land though.Normally the big storms are the ones that have come across the atlantic and had time to get the energy up. This is a really short lived hurricane and it is one of the biggest ever. Conditions must have been perfect for development.It's moved more East on the trackLooks like Manzanillo is going to get it Edited by Gandahar on Friday 23 October 18:08
